Director-General of the Bureau of Public Service Reforms (BPSR), Dasuki Ibrahim Arabi is bereaved. Arabi lost his first son, Ahmad Suyudi, at the weekend. Suyudi, a graduate of Business Administration, died after a brief illness. PRNigeria reports that the 25-year-old was buried at a Muslim cemetery in Abuja on Sunday. After his university education, Suyudi executed his National Youth Service (NYSC) with the Corporate Affairs Commission (CAC).